1
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:37,800
Thank you.

2
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:41,600
Thanks.

3
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,479
Bingchen.

4
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,479
Degong.

5
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:57,720
This marriage contract has finally returned to its rightful owner.

6
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,640
Degong.

7
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,420
That's wonderful.

8
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,120
For our children's marriage,

9
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,520
without a grand

10
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,400
wedding ceremony,

11
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:10,680
I'm truly sorry.

12
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,660
We'll definitely make it up another day.

13
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,400
Degong,

14
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,040
you're being too formal with me.

15
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:20,520
You saved my daughter's life today.

16
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,680
I, Tang Bingchen, am eternally grateful.

17
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:24,280
Good.

18
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,640
It's nothing.

19
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,360
Si Po,

20
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,880
prepare some new satin fabrics,

21
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,520
bedding,

22
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,730
and set up a proper bridal chamber.

23
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:33,650
Alright.

24
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,000
Well, Degong,

25
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,360
I'll head back now

26
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,560
to pack up Ju'er's belongings

27
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:40,880
and bring them over another day.

28
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:41,400
Good.

29
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:42,560
Take care.

30
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:50,480
Ju'er.

31
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,240
Just formally call me Dad.

32
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,320
Dad.

33
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,600
I never expected this bad situation would turn into something good.

34
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,400
Indeed.

35
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:06,500
Degong,

36
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,840
let Xia'er come with me.

37
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:11,560
Let's go, Xia'er.

38
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,090
Go ahead.

39
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,260
Take care, Uncle Tang.

40
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,240
All right.

41
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:38,240
What's going on?

42
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,040
Why did you come back?

43
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,640
The major is dead.

44
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,680
How could this be?

45
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:49,210
Why did you suddenly disappear this morning?

46
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,880
Last night,

47
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:56,760
Luo Zhiyong saw

48
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:58,680
Dajima Hao and his men

49
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,280
loading boxes of

50
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,880
explosives and gasoline onto the patrol boat.

51
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,240
I suspect the voyage was a massacre.

52
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,320
Let's talk inside.

53
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,610
So you rushed back here.

54
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,240
Have you already figured out

55
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,399
your next plan?

56
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,280
We'll still use

57
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,640
the Dajiao Censheng plane crash case

58
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,680
as our opportunity.

59
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,840
This is what Fujita is most afraid to touch.

60
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,520
The reason they released Tang Ju'er today

61
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,850
is also because of this.

62
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,480
Wumu.

63
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:48,200
Why are you back so soon?

64
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,860
Where's the Major?

65
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,300
Did you complete the mission?

66
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,130
The Major died in Shanghai.

67
00:04:56,159 --> 00:04:57,290
The mission failed.

68
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,940
Then why did you come back?

69
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,280
Today, under the pretext of escorting a witness,

70
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,320
I took the Major away from Sanzao Island.

71
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:25,250
But the mission wasn't completed.

72
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:26,480
I need to finish it.

73
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,800
I need to leave Sanzao Island again,

74
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,200
under the pretext of escorting a prisoner.

75
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,760
You mean Oshima Hiroshi?

76
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,120
Yes.

77
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:37,120
I need to take Oshima away from Sanzao Island,

78
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,080
and I also need to take you, Biying,

79
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,409
away from here with him.

80
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,159
But will Fujita really

81
00:05:43,159 --> 00:05:43,760
let us go that easily?

82
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,880
I've already laid the groundwork

83
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,210
with Commander Fujita.

84
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:46,800
Fujita has already

85
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,240
begun to suspect Oshima.

86
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,120
The most important thing for Fujita

87
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,380
is to protect himself.

88
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,360
His position

89
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,200
means more than anything to him.

90
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,520
So sacrificing one or two subordinates

91
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,880
is not an issue for him.

92
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:57,920
Especially when it's such

93
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:58,920
a hot potato.

94
00:05:59,120 --> 00:05:59,980
What I need to do

95
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,480
is convince Fujita

96
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,800
that Oshima is connected to Ogaku Mineo's plane crash

97
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,800
beyond any doubt.

98
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:05,730
This way,

99
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,280
I can naturally

100
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:08,600
use the pretext of escorting a prisoner

101
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,240
to take Oshima away from Sanzao Island

102
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,900
and remove a threat from here.

103
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,740
What I need to do now

104
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:14,880
is to find some

105
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,210
evidence that points directly to Oshima.

106
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:22,560
We could use the lifting of the maritime ban.

107
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,280
Director Shen mentioned before

108
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:24,960
that he hoped we could

109
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:27,120
use the lifting of the maritime ban to leave Sanzao Island.

110
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,650
But that's impossible now.

111
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,480
And the lifting of the maritime ban

112
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,520
itself is also problematic.

113
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,640
I also need to figure out

114
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,840
what kind of scheme Oshima is plotting.

115
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:35,480
I mentioned this matter

116
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,800
to Commander Fujita before.

117
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,400
His reaction was as if he'd just heard about it.

118
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,720
But Oshima organizing the lifting of the ban

119
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,040
without telling Fujita -

120
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,440
that doesn't make sense.

121
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,360
I think it's suspicious too.

122
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,280
So I suspect

123
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,810
Fujita knows about this

124
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:51,800
and has tacitly approved it,

125
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,200
but pretends not to know.

126
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,600
This kind of situation is very common in the military.

127
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,200
It means

128
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,159
a commander wants something done

129
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,800
but doesn't want to take responsibility.

130
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,130
You guessed correctly.

131
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,760
Translator Luo once revealed

132
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:08,360
that Oshima submitted a plan

133
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:10,560
for lifting the maritime ban to Fujita.

134
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,520
But Fujita kept it

135
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:13,240
locked in his own safe.

136
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,490
So what exactly does Fujita want to do?

137
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:20,280
Fujita used to be a diplomat.

138
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,400
In his speech,

139
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,600
he often uses diplomatic language.

140
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,330
One sentence can have multiple meanings.

141
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,920
Though vague,

142
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,720
it conceals his own views.

143
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,120
Think carefully.

144
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,920
If the maritime ban

145
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:41,290
is a grand conspiracy with Fujita's tacit approval,

146
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,460
what does that suggest to you?

147
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,800
Fujita once told me,

148
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,800
'A drop of honey catches more flies

149
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,400
than a gallon of gall.'

150
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,520
'A drop of honey catches more flies

151
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,780
than a gallon of gall.'

152
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:01,800
He used to say this

153
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,400
to Oshima Hiroshi many times.

154
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,040
But Oshima

155
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,170
insisted on using gall to catch flies.

156
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,760
This saying was originally

157
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:10,480
from President Lincoln.

158
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,920
It refers to an appeasement policy.

159
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:16,240
Gall

160
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,780
refers to harsh measures.

161
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,160
So lifting the maritime ban

162
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,680
seems beneficial to villagers on the surface.

163
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,680
This is the honey.

164
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,880
But the honey contains gall inside.

165
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,840
Fujita went to Dahengqin Island today

166
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,160
and won't return until tomorrow.

167
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,080
So tonight,

168
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,980
I will do whatever it takes

169
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,039
to get the maritime ban lifting plan.

170
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,679
All right.

171
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,600
I'll go prepare.

172
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,360
Wait.

173
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,650
I'll go with you.

174
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:50,040
It's been four years.

175
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,160
The Japanese

176
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:55,200
choose this particular moment to lift the maritime ban.

177
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,200
And they've also registered

178
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:59,280
all the young men on the island.

179
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:03,360
If your guess is correct,

180
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:07,360
the bitterness of gall is already at our lips.

181
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:12,200
Mr. Ye, please remain calm.

182
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,000
Let's wait until I get accurate information,

183
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,860
then we can discuss our next move.

184
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:25,800
Dad,

185
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,260
we'll be going now.

186
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:28,520
Go ahead.

187
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,320
I know what I need to do.

188
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:58,620
You don't need to worry about convincing me.

189
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:01,960
I wasn't trying to convince you.

190
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,200
I know

191
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,800
lifting the maritime ban might be a conspiracy

192
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,210
that threatens the islanders' lives.

193
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:12,960
But

194
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,840
the most important thing right now

195
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,760
is to get this intelligence out.

196
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,400
This is too cruel for you.

197
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:27,240
I remember you said before

198
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,540
that you wanted to add some weight to my life.

199
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:32,500
I didn't understand then.

200
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,200
But I understand now.

201
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:40,680
Reality is far more brutal

202
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,600
than I ever imagined.

203
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,120
It's okay.

204
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,000
Thank you.

205
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:03,640
Don't mention it.

206
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:49,280
Did the major say anything before he died?

207
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,650
We didn't have time to say goodbye.

208
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,860
Inoue Akira's men surrounded us.

209
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:58,760
He pulled the self-destruct device

210
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,120
and died on the spot.

211
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,160
Next.

212
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:00,400
Do you know what kind of responsibility

213
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:02,600
we are carrying?

214
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,690
The Bible you asked me to memorize,

215
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,680
I've memorized it all.

216
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,800
That's just the master copy.

217
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,760
The Major told me

218
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,940
the decryption code on the plane.

219
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:18,560
What exactly is the mission?

220
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:21,920
The Major told me.

221
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,680
America will send

222
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,080
a bombing squadron of B-25 bombers

223
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,720
to raid Tokyo.

224
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:29,840
After the raid,

225
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,080
these planes

226
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,140
will land at Quzhou Airport in China.

227
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,480
The code the Major was carrying

228
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,480
The call signs and radio beacons

229
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,770
are meant to guide these aircraft.

230
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,400
If they cannot be delivered

231
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,520
before April 18th,

232
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,280
these planes won't be able to land safely

233
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,840
at Quzhou Airport.

234
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:46,820
Therefore,

235
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:48,320
what we need to do

236
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,840
is to leave Sanzao Island as soon as possible,

237
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,100
get to Quzhou Airport,

238
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,540
and welcome these returning heroes.

239
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:07,480
Sergeant.

240
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,240
Aren't you going to

241
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,880
tell us something?

242
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:15,280
Those Army pilots are tight-lipped.

243
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,680
Can't get anything out of them.

244
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:17,480
You know what?

245
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,640
Everyone on the ship is betting

246
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:21,840
on where these pilots are headed.

247
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,480
Some say Manila,

248
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:24,560
some say Midway,

249
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,780
and some say Japan.

250
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,280
I put my money on Japan.

251
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,080
But I also heard

252
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,520
it might be Alaska.

253
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,420
You want to bet on that?

254
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,120
You might make a fortune.

255
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,560
Alaska?

256
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,360
Obviously,

257
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,290
Lieutenant Miller is from Alaska.

258
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,720
There's a rumor that

259
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:43,480
the Army picked him for the Aleutians

260
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,360
for a secret mission.

261
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,000
All right.

262
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,120
I'll put 20 bucks on Alaska.

263
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:48,720
You got it.

264
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,000
Now get back to work.

265
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:55,080
Hey!

266
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,010
Not bad, Richie.

267
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,240
I heard they're going to bomb Japan.

268
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,040
Now we have to be

269
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:58,760
on their side.

270
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,280
Great.

271
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,000
Coming to Philadelphia,

272
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,060
I'm your buddy now.

273
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,050
I'll step away for a moment.

274
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:11,040
Cleaner!

275
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:12,880
Do you have any water

276
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,200
so I can wash my plane?

277
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:16,560
Here you go.

278
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:18,170
What?

279
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,250
You're welcome.

280
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:20,900
What's wrong with you?

281
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,280
Fresh water on the ship is limited.

282
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:28,720
If you newcomers don't like it,

283
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:29,640
here,

284
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,100
go get seawater yourself.

285
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,360
Here's some soap for you.

286
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:39,520
Come on!

287
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,520
You don't even know what you're doing,

288
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,180
Army pilot!

289
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:45,400
Come on!

290
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:48,960
Come on!

291
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:55,600
We need to break them up.

292
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:00,040
